PrecisPROVINCIAL EMERGENCIES FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE ORDER No. 6 - which declares the severe flooding in and around the Perth-Andover area of NEW BRUNSWICK that began on or about April 12, 1993, to be of concern to the federal government and authorizes the provision of financial assistance to the Province in respect thereof.
